The paper also discusses the use of static and dynamic oracles for training the algorithm, which suggests that cs.LG (Learning) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) are possible categories. Finally, the paper mentions the use of the Wall Street Journal section from the English Penn Treebank and the Penn Chinese Treebank, which suggests that cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is a possible category as well, as these are commonly used datasets in natural language processing research.
